This paper deals with the study of words and their factorizations, which is a topic in formal language theory (cs.FL). The concept of generalized Lyndon words is closely related to the lexicographic order, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves the use of combinatorial techniques to study the properties of these words, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM) and combinatorics (cs.CC).
